In this statement, the President expresses gratitude to Interior Secretary Ken Salazar for his hard work and leadership. The President commends Salazar for his efforts in conserving the nation's land, water, and wildlife and for promoting responsible development of domestic energy resources. Salazar's work in renewable energy projects and oil and gas production has been guided by science and safety standards. Additionally, Salazar has made significant progress in strengthening the relationship with Indian Country and resolving disputes to make tribal communities safer and stronger. The President also mentions his personal friendship with Salazar and states that he will continue to seek his counsel even after he returns to his home state of Colorado.